aa(lp328
VSo the question is, is there any hope for adoption of something like this,
p329
aVwhich would presumably save a lot of lives?
p330
aVAnd I think the answer, perhaps, lies in a story.
p331
aVThe answer both to why has a car seat been so successful,
p332
aVand why this may someday be adopted or not,
p333
aVlies in a story that my dad told me, relating to when he was a doctor
p334
aVin the U.S. Air Force in England. And this is a long time ago:
p335
aVyou were allowed to do things then you can't do today.
p336
aVSo, my father would have patients come in
p337
aVwho he thought were not really sick.
p338
aVAnd he had a big jar full of placebo pills that he would give them,
p339
aVand he'd say, "Come back in a week, if you still feel lousy."
p340
aVOK, and most of them would not come back,
p341
aVbut some of them would come back.
p342
aVAnd when they came back, he, still convinced they were not sick,
p343
aVhad another jar of pills. In this jar were huge horse pills.
p344
aVThey were almost impossible to swallow.
p345
aVAnd these, to me, are the analogy for the car seats.
p346
aVPeople would look at these and say, "Man, this thing is so big
p347
aVand so hard to swallow. If this doesn't make me feel better,
p348
aVyou know, what possibly could?"
p349
aa(lp350
VAnd it turned out that most people wouldn't come back,
p351
aVbecause it worked. But every once in a while,
p352
aVthere was still a patient convinced that he was sick,
p353
aVand he'd come back. And my dad had a third jar of pills.
p354
aVAnd the jar of pills he had, he said,
p355
aVwere the tiniest little pills he could find,
p356
aVso small you could barely see them.
p357
aVAnd he would say, listen, I know I gave you that huge pill,
p358
aVthat complicated, hard-to-swallow pill before,
p359
aVbut now I've got one that's so potent,
p360
aVthat is really tiny and small and almost invisible.
p361
aVIt's almost like this thing here, which you can't even see."
p362
aa(lp363
VAnd it turned out that never,
p364
aVin all the times my dad gave out this pill, the really tiny pill,
p365
aVdid anyone ever come back still complaining of sickness.
p366
aVSo, my dad always took that as evidence
p367
aVthat this little, teeny, powerful pill
p368
aVhad the ultimate placebo effect. And in some sense, if that's the right story,
p369
aVI think integrated car seats you will see, very quickly,
p370
aVbecoming something that everyone has. The other possible conclusion
p371
aVis, well, maybe after coming to my father three times,
p372
aVgetting sent home with placebos, he still felt sick,
p373
aVhe went and found another doctor.
p374
aVAnd that's completely possible. And if that's the case,
p375
aVthen I think we're stuck with conventional car seats for a long time to come.
p376
aVThank you very much.
